WEBVTT

00:10.946 --> 00:12.608
Thank you Curtis, Mr. Whitley.

00:12.628 --> 00:16.614
I tell you, he's got a lot more nerve than I've got.

00:16.894 --> 00:20.359
He had never led a song before until just a few months ago.

00:21.220 --> 00:22.682
That's something I cannot do.

00:22.963 --> 00:23.764
I will not do.

00:23.784 --> 00:28.050
I've been around for 40, 50 years, but I guarantee I don't want to run people off.

00:30.473 --> 00:31.855
The Curtis has done a good job.

00:31.875 --> 00:33.938
He's got a lot of guts.

00:36.386 --> 00:37.467
Good to see you guys.

00:37.567 --> 00:43.315
I'll tell you what, it's good to see anybody nowadays after a week's worth of snow and ice.

00:45.357 --> 00:47.980
We don't have a near as bad as they do back east.

00:48.461 --> 00:54.809
18 wheelers cars, two or three hundred cars pile up at once and for hours.

00:54.829 --> 01:00.116
A lot of the people up there are still a hundred thousands of people without power.

01:01.157 --> 01:05.202
So we're doing pretty good here, relatively speaking.

01:06.114 --> 01:22.175
And I brought the, I'm still having to do everything I bought a printer here a while back so I could start printing my stuff up like I used to.

01:22.695 --> 01:27.802
Well, I got a home and started taking it out of the box and it said you had to have at least windows 10 or 11 to do it.

01:28.363 --> 01:29.304
So I had to take it back.

01:29.404 --> 01:33.970
So now I'm still doing the cutting paste, but it's good for me.

01:35.746 --> 01:38.770
Gratitude, I decided it's last minute.

01:38.790 --> 01:40.993
I thought I'd been preparing all this.

01:41.053 --> 01:42.815
What does gratitude really mean?

01:43.016 --> 01:54.190
Well, one of the dictionary says, gratitude is a quality of being grateful, quality of being grateful, an emotion of the heart.

01:56.073 --> 01:59.257
And sometimes gratitude can be the emotion of the heart.

02:00.659 --> 02:03.282
Excited by a favor received,

02:04.066 --> 02:05.188
Have you all been that way?

02:05.308 --> 02:10.495
I'm sure most of you have had at least a little bit in thankfulness.

02:15.342 --> 02:19.889
I've been, this is a subject I've been thinking about for quite a while, you know, for a couple of years or so.

02:19.909 --> 02:29.362
And I think even the older I get in the age, the more I think about being grateful for things that I can still do.

02:31.874 --> 02:43.605
The Bible speaks a lot about gratitude and about thankfulness and thinking of this nature, and I'm sure Mr. Whit will mention some of those things in his message.

02:43.625 --> 02:48.338
I didn't know what he was going to preach about, but it's a very important part

02:48.770 --> 02:53.458
of his subject, I think, by what talks about gratitude.

02:53.538 --> 02:55.541
Today I'm going to cover just a few things.

02:55.561 --> 03:01.692
There's so many scriptures and some I leave out, you know, you're going to think of some even better.

03:02.032 --> 03:11.648
So there's a lot of scriptures has to do with having gratitude and being thankful for the things that we have.

03:12.249 --> 03:14.994
And a lot of times things that we don't have

03:17.634 --> 03:25.307
I've got about 10 points, and that's just scratching the surface of many different things that can be expressed there.

03:25.387 --> 03:29.995
I know you've got many of them there, and I've only got so long to do this.

03:33.500 --> 03:39.250
Number one I've got on my deal is thank God for His creation.

03:39.362 --> 03:50.499
Here a few weeks ago, my last message I gave on one of the scriptures was Psalms 138, I'm sorry, 139 verse 14.

03:51.500 --> 03:53.243
And I'm just gonna quote the family.

03:53.263 --> 03:57.870
And David said, I'm so fearfully and wonderfully made.

03:58.931 --> 04:08.786
And you look at the body, every different parts of the body, so many intricate parts of the body, you know, and the way God made it,

04:09.154 --> 04:10.917
I'd like to have one more arm sometime.

04:10.937 --> 04:17.029
There was a guy in the gym that they were putting up a new paper towel dispenser and he needed one more hand to do it.

04:17.109 --> 04:18.071
