04:18.131 --> 04:22.981
I didn't want to insult him, but he really needed one more hand to get the screws out of that other one.

04:23.522 --> 04:29.012
He must have had a problem because I come back the next time I worked out and they had a big hole in the seat rock there.

04:30.034 --> 04:32.018
I probably should have offered to help him.

04:32.834 --> 04:36.419
But anyway, our body is fearfully and wonderfully made.

04:36.479 --> 04:39.063
God knows we only need two arms and two hands.

04:39.143 --> 04:41.166
He knows our eye needs to be in front of us.

04:41.667 --> 04:44.911
He knows our nose needs to be right here.

04:45.272 --> 04:48.176
I think God knew too for the many things that we have.

04:52.402 --> 04:57.890
I'm grateful, and I think most of you are too, about the book of instruction, the Bible.

04:58.090 --> 05:00.594
It tells us how to do it right.

05:00.930 --> 05:04.375
You know, if you buy a new automobile, you buy a new washing machine or something.

05:04.916 --> 05:08.742
And it comes with an instruction book on how to make that work right.

05:09.643 --> 05:14.951
Most people know that you don't put sugar in a gas tank unless you want to lock their engine up.

05:15.131 --> 05:16.533
People used to do that years ago.

05:16.553 --> 05:21.080
They didn't matter somebody, they'd pour five pounds of sugar in their gas tank.

05:21.100 --> 05:23.463
I don't know how much it took to end up.

05:23.543 --> 05:28.511
But anyway, that's something that we don't...

05:28.871 --> 05:30.834
Excuse me.

05:31.138 --> 05:34.904
Thankful for God's instruction book.

05:37.327 --> 05:43.857
And he says Psalms 119 verse 105, and I'm going paraphrase that.

05:43.877 --> 05:46.001
Well, let me see, I could go to that, I think I've got him.

05:47.884 --> 05:52.330
And so the Bible's getting so, that pages getting a little rickety.

05:55.195 --> 05:56.096
But I still like it.

05:57.118 --> 05:59.922
Psalms 119.

06:01.570 --> 06:09.842
and verse 105, thy word is a lamp unto my feet and a light unto my path.

06:11.004 --> 06:18.956
This is metaphorically, but even physically, having a light is so beneficial.

06:19.056 --> 06:28.210
I may come in here a few years ago, and I mentioned this one thing that we were visiting with one of our daughters out in

06:28.706 --> 06:31.109
Way out in the mountains in California.

06:31.149 --> 06:35.874
Way back in there, it was dark and I mentioned this about not having a line.

06:35.894 --> 06:42.280
I had to get up and go to the bathroom and they have our bedroom that's reserved for us when we go out there.

06:42.321 --> 06:46.485
And right around the corner, it's not very far as the bathroom.

06:47.466 --> 06:50.209
Well, they didn't have any nightlights on them.

06:50.269 --> 06:54.994
I guess they went out or something and I went around and went in there and all of a sudden,

06:55.074 --> 06:59.819
hit something with all five of my toes, a big toe and a little toe and everything.

06:59.859 --> 07:00.800
Boy, did that hurt.

07:01.580 --> 07:02.741
And I thought, where am I?

07:02.982 --> 07:05.824
And so I can reach down and see if I can move it and get it out of the way.

07:05.864 --> 07:09.208
And I stuck my hand in the toilet bowl.

07:11.730 --> 07:13.892
I embarrassed my son and awesome.

07:13.912 --> 07:18.056
I said, he put my lights all down around the place, even in our bedroom.

07:19.117 --> 07:21.820
But I thought, well, you know, this is a good analogy.

07:22.200 --> 07:24.082
How many things do we do in life?

07:24.610 --> 07:32.721
If we just had light, if we just knew how to handle this situation, some of the young people, they don't know what to do, you know, about certain situations.

07:33.422 --> 07:35.064
They hook up, they do this, they do that.

07:35.084 --> 07:38.289
And so, you know, God's Word is a light to our path.

07:38.389 --> 07:45.098
And instead of the candle, the word lamp, and I think Hebrew said candle.

07:45.158 --> 07:51.186
So, you know, we need a little night light for little things.

07:53.890 --> 07:56.092
I'm grateful for necessities of life.

07:56.212 --> 08:11.288
There's so many things that we really need to have and there's so many scriptures that they explain to us how important that we don't have to worry about those that Jesus said, seek you first, the kingdom of God in Matthew 6, 33.

08:11.328 --> 08:13.550
And all these things may be added to you.

08:14.371 --> 08:21.298
Well, in Psalms 37, there was a scripture that Mr. Gregory, our used to be pastor,

08:21.442 --> 08:31.457
would refer to quite often, and we were both a lot younger, but he was older than I was, or he was older than me, Mr. Lawrence Gregory.

08:32.519 --> 08:35.864
Psalms 37, verse 23, verse 23.

08:41.332 --> 08:50.866
The steps of a good man are ordered by the Lord, and he delights in his way.

08:51.234 --> 08:59.368
Verse 24, though he falls, he shall not be utterly cast down, for the Lord upholds him with his hand.

08:59.408 --> 09:13.311
There's a part that Mr. Gregory would say, and I can, amen, I can get over that any day, because I agree, says verse 25, I have been young.

09:13.331 --> 09:17.458
At one time I was young,

09:17.538 --> 09:21.923
You young guys out here, there's Maddox.

09:22.043 --> 09:23.705
I was 15 at one time.

09:23.725 --> 09:27.770
I was telling Maddox, he has a better mustache than I had when I was 15.

09:28.931 --> 09:30.513
I'd go in there and shave, you know.

09:30.553 --> 09:33.617
Everybody ain't trying to get, I heard if you save more than they'd grow.

09:33.637 --> 09:35.539
Well, he's got a good mustache and I didn't.

09:36.801 --> 09:40.986
Now I'm going to wait the spring so I can cut the rest of this off.

09:41.006 --> 09:41.767
You have to get a spring.

09:41.787 --> 09:44.690
But anyway, oh.

09:44.834 --> 09:54.227
I have been young and now I'm old yet I have not seen the righteous forsaken nor his seed begging bread.

09:54.267 --> 10:08.226
And that my wife and I, we started a lot of, you know, we started our business of the cleaning service, cleaning anything with the ceilings of the floor and even the driveway and everything else.

10:08.266 --> 10:13.874
When I was about 29 years old, we had five kids and people that I would

10:14.210 --> 10:25.203
talk about going into business and say, well, David, most companies, it takes three to five years before you can really start making a living at it, before you start doing okay.

10:25.884 --> 10:28.266
I said, yeah, that's right for most people.

10:28.326 --> 10:35.134
I thought God was gonna hand me business, gonna hand me jobs, they'll have to write, well, it didn't happen.

10:36.015 --> 10:39.319
We went dumpster diving at times.

10:39.840 --> 10:41.682
We had one particular job,

10:42.306 --> 10:43.567
And it was a nasty job.

10:43.628 --> 10:48.453
Every two weeks, we had a clean bar.

10:48.513 --> 10:50.856
The Woodland Mountains, they were out on 51st Street.

10:50.896 --> 10:51.737
It's not there anymore.

10:51.757 --> 10:54.060
They've redone the intersection.

10:54.941 --> 10:58.405
And we took over five kids in there.

10:58.545 --> 11:01.068
They closed the bars up at two o'clock in the morning.

11:02.049 --> 11:09.938
And we'd go in there and they told us, well, anybody you find, not the register, but any money you find, you can have.

11:10.306 --> 11:11.768
We cleaned everything.

11:11.788 --> 11:18.054
We'd have, my wife usually would take their glasses off of the mirror back there and clean the deals.

11:18.695 --> 11:33.371
You know, the glass plates, some mirrors, they'd be streaked and some of the kids would go through the booze and sometimes they'd find a little money that fell out of somebody's pocket and that was a blessing.

11:34.272 --> 11:39.858
And one time, one of the kids found a whole bag of quarters

11:40.578 --> 11:41.680
And we took them literally.

11:41.720 --> 11:44.164
They said, any money that you find out here, you can have.

11:44.384 --> 11:46.367
So we had a good breakfast when we got home.

11:46.928 --> 11:49.031
We'd get through about seven o'clock in the morning.

11:50.013 --> 11:56.122
And sometimes it'd be vomit that they missed the stool and get it on the wall and get it on the floor.

11:56.142 --> 11:57.144
It was a nasty job.

11:57.224 --> 11:58.766
And we didn't get paid that much.

11:59.627 --> 12:03.534
And we couldn't afford to drop the job because we needed the money.

12:04.395 --> 12:09.042
But anyway, we were still thankful for the job.

12:09.730 --> 12:12.212
And we're thankful that God helped us to get out of that.

12:12.252 --> 12:18.238
We learned an awful lot about human relations, about business, about a lot of things.

12:19.400 --> 12:21.682
But anyway, we had never been forsaken.

12:21.722 --> 12:22.943
We never missed a meal.

12:22.983 --> 12:31.431
Had a lot of cornbread and beans and cornbread milk and potatoes that God never made us go to be hungry.

12:33.373 --> 12:38.098
We need to be grateful and I am, and I'm sure you are too about it.

12:38.242 --> 12:40.565
all of our essential benefits.

12:40.585 --> 12:43.770
We have a lot of benefits that we really need.

12:43.830 --> 12:47.755
