16:57.475 --> 17:02.802
You know, sometimes you get blessings you don't ask for, I have.

17:03.266 --> 17:08.872
There was a few years ago, I don't know, three, four years ago, two or three, I don't remember, and I'd lose track of time.

17:09.573 --> 17:16.240
But I'd had my first knee surgeries in the summer time, and we had a lot of rain, and the grass was really growing.

17:17.161 --> 17:23.328
And I just had the, like I said, with knee surgeries, taking physical therapy, and what was that rough?

17:24.469 --> 17:32.658
And a couple here in the church, and all of you guys know, and I asked for permission to use our name,

17:32.866 --> 17:39.814
Trevor and Chrissy paid their lawn care people to mow my yard.

17:41.095 --> 17:43.137
I didn't ask to do that.

17:43.157 --> 17:45.480
I didn't tell them I couldn't do that.

17:45.960 --> 17:49.684
They just did that and they were going to do it all summer if I needed it.

17:50.185 --> 17:57.833
Two weeks later I got out there and I moved my own grass because I knew Trevor and Chrissy would do that and I know some of you would have done the same thing.

17:57.893 --> 18:02.258
There's not a person in here that I wouldn't trust if I asked something.

18:02.434 --> 18:05.678
that I would not think that you'd do it right.

18:05.779 --> 18:07.301
You'd do me something.

18:08.102 --> 18:09.744
We have the brethren here.

18:10.105 --> 18:13.990
I wouldn't trade you guys for 10,000 others out in the world.

18:14.010 --> 18:14.751
I really wouldn't.

18:15.893 --> 18:20.539
And Fran and I are grateful too for our neighbors.

18:21.320 --> 18:25.406
We've been in the same house for 54 years coming up in March.

18:26.327 --> 18:31.474
And the neighbor across the street, they've had several different people over the years.

18:32.002 --> 18:42.138
But there's one couple of, well, they have their son living with them too, and I think the mother, his mother, so there's three generations live directly across the road from us.

18:43.140 --> 18:57.042
And about a year after the knee surgery, I had back surgery, and a hot water heater had gone out, and it was in the garage.

18:57.698 --> 19:01.842
And I'd already bought the hot water heater and it was in the back of the pickup.

19:01.882 --> 19:04.165
I had the bed of the pickup of the door.

19:04.305 --> 19:07.428
I mean, whatever it is, the back, the lip down door.

19:07.488 --> 19:12.093
And two-wheeled dolly out there, ready to put it in.

19:12.113 --> 19:15.396
And I had my two-legged dolly standing beside me, friend.

19:16.357 --> 19:25.106
And my two-legged daughter said, I mean, my two-legged dolly, not dolly, pardon, my two-legged dolly.

19:25.602 --> 19:26.804
said, how do you get this?

19:26.904 --> 19:29.628
And I said, well, let's talk about it.

19:30.149 --> 19:32.653
And I leaned on the two-hill dolly.

19:33.514 --> 19:40.525
And neighbors directly across the street were six to go to work, the young guy and his son.

19:40.545 --> 19:43.690
He said, hey, David, you need some help.

19:43.810 --> 19:49.298
And I said, no, my two-hill, I mean, my two-legged dolly said, why did you say that?

19:49.922 --> 19:52.406
I said, well, he's got to go to work.

19:52.566 --> 19:55.972
And so he said, David, you need some help.

19:55.992 --> 19:58.255
I said, OK, yeah, for a little bit.

19:58.275 --> 19:59.377
So he ordered his son.

19:59.397 --> 20:00.098
They come over.

20:01.580 --> 20:06.709
I was wondering how to get it in, get the box out, and take it around to the side of the Rob's door.

20:07.430 --> 20:17.746
And the new codes, which has been there for a while, you have to have the hot water heater 18 inches off the floor because of the fumes and all that.

20:17.826 --> 20:19.729
I thought, man, I don't know how to do that.

20:21.693 --> 20:22.654
But I would determine.

20:23.335 --> 20:25.980
They took it out of the pickup, took the box off of it.

20:26.741 --> 20:29.686
They didn't even use the two-wheel volley.

20:30.908 --> 20:32.671
They picked it up and carried it around.

20:32.691 --> 20:36.337
They took it into the side door of the garage and squeezed their way around.

20:36.718 --> 20:43.730
They opened a little closet back there where the air-conditioning heating unit and the hot water heater is, and they set it up on that pedestal.

20:45.058 --> 20:46.961
You talk about a blessing.

20:47.201 --> 20:48.022
Talk about a blessing.

20:48.042 --> 21:03.523
I didn't ask for it, and there are Hispanic people, and he speaks and understands it pretty good, but sometimes we have to get around to his broken English, and he stood up there in the undergrabs, and he pointed at me.

21:03.563 --> 21:08.370
He said, any time you need some help, you can knock, knock, knock, knock on my door.

21:08.898 --> 21:16.087
I said, okay, and he said, no, I mean, he said, anytime you need help, he'd knock knock knock knock knock on my door and I'll come right away and I'll help you.

21:16.928 --> 21:19.211
You know, that was, that was amazing.

21:19.792 --> 21:20.733
That was amazing.

21:21.634 --> 21:33.049
The back one, the deal I was talking about in my yard, I didn't want to act unbreakable, but it was hard for me to, I'd tell him thank you and then walk off, you know, my wife was that.

21:33.630 --> 21:36.914
But it was about at least two years before I could tell Trevor

21:37.250 --> 21:43.099
how it really felt about that, you know, without breaking up.

21:44.181 --> 21:46.284
And I thought I'm strong enough now to do that.

21:47.305 --> 21:54.356
And during the talking, I began to tear up and my voice was beginning to break and I just turned around and walked off.

21:54.396 --> 21:59.864
You know, it meant so much to me, the people in our church that way.

